				<td colspan="2"><span>If i had to do it all over again, i would still keep a woodelf becuase they kick a$ (LOL), but put all my points into STA and rest into INT.
<br />

<br />
CHA gear is a dime a dozen, but STA is expensive and crtical at higher lvl.
<br />

<br />
The real question to ask is what bard do you want to be mostly?  We can adapt to it all but put your base stats into what you want to do mostly.  If you are battle bard go with a human and max STA.  If you are mez/charm then go with woodelf and max CHA.  
<br />

<br />
I did a combo of CHA/DEX/INT but not STA as a woodelf.   I made a mistake when creating my bard (i read casters realm for creation *BONK*)  But i am sure not gonna start him over now<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />

<br />
just my 2cp</span></td>
