				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New Bard<a name="17953"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 04 8:59 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Illusions wont fix your faction but they will change your base faction.  For example, I a half elf agnostic who has never killed an honest iksar (those pesky outcasts are another matter) can get illusion iksar from my mask and walk around in cabillis (until it fades that is).
<br />

<br />
As far as stats go they have different utility at different levels.  If you think you will solo through the 30s &amp; 40s then int and chr are important - however it will cost you later to build up your stamina.  If you are like me and play a couple of hours/wk then those two are what worked for me.  If you plan of becoming time flagged in two weeks then Sta is the way to go.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
