				<td colspan="2"><span>I made an agnostic HE bard and split the starting points between DEX and CHA.  I don't believe it's made any significant difference.  CHA gear is relatively easy to find and we are unclear as to what levels are really optimal.  Dex is supposed ot make it easier to sing while being hit I believe, but that's tough to verify.    
<br />

<br />
Stamina stat gear used to be difficult to find.  However, with the advent of LDoN, many items have +8 to +15 STA on them.  The net result is that even with a beginning STA of 70, my bard could get STA to 250 with the right gear purchases.  
