				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes, sta is important, but it's still not the be all end all that everyone makes it out to be.  
<br />

<br />
Dex gear isn't too hard to come by, and most everyone is looking for harness or focus or whatever, and that gives a large boost to dex.  Most times with a decent set of equipment you are going to be fairly high dex and the shammie buff will put you at max. 
<br />

<br />
There is a huge huge huge amount of sta stuff in the game, Verant listened, and pretty much everything now will have sta as well as hp or hp/mana.
<br />

<br />
There is not as much cha stuff.   LDoN is a help, but that just allows you to stick cha on gear that has sta or hps or both. :p
<br />

<br />
Heck, my &quot;dream&quot; profile (I didn't list any time stuff except the bp) wouldn't max out my cha if I had all the levels of planar power.  And that's picking mostly stuff that has Cha on it too.  It would max my sta (with an extra 85 points) and my int (by 37 points).   
<br />

<br />
So, points into Sta to get to base 75 (which I didn't do when I started, 75 is a magic number for sta) and the rest into Cha.  If your sta is already 75, then max points to cha and the rest whereever you feel like it. ;)
<br />

<br />
I think maybe I'll work up a dream list with time gear and see how much sillier my profile looks. :p</span></td>
