				<td colspan="2"><span>Edit: Bah, just read Steppy's guide and it is right on....although you could skip to the last paragraph and do just fine.
<br />

<br />
It doesn't matter.
<br />

<br />
You will wish you had more of any stat you don't pump up (cept wisdom). Low on any stat will cause you grief, while really high is not that great a benefit, in most cases, although I am hearing and have experiienced high/maxed charisma in some circumstances is very handy.
<br />

<br />
I have the ability to alter my stats on my FV bard between stamina/hp/str/ and charisma/int. Last night I did the stalker camp and survived a hit and stun from the full swarm (at 52, got away with 3%--thats 2900hp of damage). On the other hand, with 132 charisma and FT1 I ran out of mana before I could complete three cycles....lots of resists and early breaks, even with the bs flute equipped.
<br />

<br />
Next time I'll switch to int/charisma gear. If it makes a huge difference, I'll post. 
<br />

<br />
Kitties, and to some extent humans can suffer size problems.
<br />

<br />
Nite blindness (human) can be a nuisance, but can be dealt with.
<br />

<br />
If you wanna make/wear cultural armor at some point, then choose diety based on that. To be honest, there is good non-cultural gear that competes at most levels with the cultural smithed stuff in price and stats.
<br />

<br />
Stamina is very important but half of peoples complaints revolve around the difficulty of raising it with gear, as opposed to being level 65 with 3khp vs 3200 unbuffed.
<br />

<br />
After all that, see the first line. (I have 3 bards with vastly varying stats).</span></td>
