				<td colspan="2"><span>lots of good info here.
<br />

<br />
to be blunt with regaurds to race, diety, it does not really matter to much.
<br />

<br />
the halfelf rallos zek bard is nice, then you can use the higher end RZ armor, but you can get armor much like that from LDoN too out of NRo.
<br />

<br />
i have mucked around with a wood elf, half elf, and have a 55th vah shir bard.
<br />

<br />
love my kitty for its base stats (but i have changed so many of them with gear now it does not matter) and the inate safe fall.  this is a life saver i will say.  but a HUGE drawback to my kitty is the fact that im a large race.  this means a lot of gear does not fit me, and i do not fit in those blasted small doors of the elves.  makes things a bit of a pain at times, but oh well.  thats life.
<br />

<br />
play what you will be happy with.
<br />

<br />
if you are not twinking (and i never sujest twinking a bard unti you know the class) there are a few stats that are rather important to the bard.
<br />

<br />
CHA = reduces chance of missed notes (fizzle) and infulences your ability to charm/lull 
<br />

<br />
STA = HP, and HP = life  enough said
<br />

<br />
Dex = supposed to be a back up for CHA on missed notes and is supposed to be a checker for when stopping/starting songs or when hit to prevent interupts.
<br />

<br />
INT = for mana pool.  some of your best songs will use small amounts of mana, others large amounts.  FM(faiding memories, bard FD type song/skill) uses something like 900 or 800 mana so you can see where having a large mana pool would be nice.
<br />

<br />
FT items are also nice to help replenish your mana.  nothing else will effect your mana regen other then FT items.
<br />

<br />
play and enjoy a great class.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
