			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New Bard<a name="18101"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 04 4:42 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In terms of races, it's really not that important in the end.  None of the races have significant downsides in endgame playability, or anything to really make them stand out.
<br />

<br />
Religion is likewise more or less irrelevant.
<br />

<br />
I went human of Rallos Zek for a few reasons, including the availability of Fierce Heraldic armor (which I'm still mostly wearing) and the fact that RZ is more or less a neutral god -- both good and evil races have RZ worshippers, so it doesn't get you in trouble anywhere except Kaladim, and I'm no longer KOS to the dwarves with maybe an hour of time and 40 pp to fix it.
<br />

<br />
One nice side bonus to being RZ was I was not default KOS to the Velious giants (though I since blew that), and I'm only &quot;Threatening&quot; in PoTactics -- with invis and Selo's on, I've been able to run all the way to the Vallon Zek chamber through a full pop.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
